trend_summary: 2000s-2020s imagery shows limited growth: scattered new houses fill gaps in the southern peninsula and around the marina, modest road extensions appear, while agricultural clearings on the northern neck shrink as tree cover spreads. The marina is refurbished, and shoreline accretion/erosion alters tidal flats, yet overall land-use stays low-intensity suburban.
notable_changes: New dwellings inserted among existing grid in southern peninsula
Boat slips and hard-standing expanded at central marina
Former crop fields in northwest show regrowth of tree cover
Minor new cul-de-sac roads added near shoreline housing
Visible shift of mudflat extent along eastern shoreline
